  "prompt": "Which is the best DSLR under 2500?",
  "response": "Finding the best DSLR under $2,500 depends on your specific needs, such as whether you prioritize resolution, speed, video capabilities, or portability. Here are some excellent options within that budget:\n\n### 1. **Canon EOS 90D**\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - 32.5 MP APS-C sensor\n     - 10 fps continuous shooting\n     - 4K video without crop\n     - Dual Pixel CMOS AF for fast and accurate autofocus\n   - **Best For**: Enthusiasts who want a high-resolution APS-C sensor and fast performance for both photography and video.\n\n### 2. **Nikon D780**\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - 24.5 MP full-frame sensor\n     - 7 fps continuous shooting (12 fps in Live View)\n     - 4K video recording\n     - Excellent low-light performance\n   - **Best For**: Photographers who want a versatile full-frame DSLR with hybrid performance for both stills and video.\n\n### 3. **Canon EOS 6D Mark II**\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - 26.2 MP full-frame sensor\n     - 6.5 fps continuous shooting\n     - Dual Pixel CMOS AF for smooth autofocus in live view and video\n     - Vari-angle touchscreen\n   - **Best For**: Travel and portrait photographers who want a lightweight full-frame DSLR.\n\n### 4. **Pentax K-1 Mark II**\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - 36.4 MP full-frame sensor\n     - Built-in 5-axis image stabilization\n     - Weather-sealed body\n     - Unique features like AstroTracer for astrophotography\n   - **Best For**: Landscape photographers and those who need a rugged, feature-rich DSLR.\n\n### 5. **Nikon D500**\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - 20.9 MP APS-C sensor\n     - 10 fps continuous shooting\n     - 4K video recording\n     - Advanced 153-point autofocus system\n   - **Best For**: Action and wildlife photographers who need speed and precision.\n\n### 6. **Canon EOS 5D Mark IV (Used/Refurbished)**\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - 30.4 MP full-frame sensor\n     - 7 fps continuous shooting\n     - 4K video recording\n     - Dual Pixel CMOS AF\n   - **Best For**: Professional photographers who want a reliable and versatile full-frame DSLR.\n\n### Recommendation:\nIf you're looking for a **new** DSLR under $2,500, the **Nikon D780** is an excellent all-rounder with its full-frame sensor and hybrid capabilities. For **APS-C**, the **Canon 90D** offers outstanding resolution and speed. If you're open to **used or refurbished** models, the **Canon 5D Mark IV** is a fantastic option with professional-grade features.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
